content.contentDesc:
M: You look unhappy, Henry. What makes you so sad?

W: My mother promised to buy me a new car, but she took back what she said yesterday.

M: Why?

W: She said it is dangerous for me to drive to school.

M: She's right. Though sixteen-year-olds are allowed to drive, it still too dangerous for us to drive on the road. Don't worry. You can talk with her about it again. Maybe you can ask her to buy you a new bike instead.

W: OK. That sounds good.

subContents.content: What may the girl get at last?

chapInfos.chap_info: 请听一段材料，完成2个小题。

question_boxs.description: 听对话，将表格所缺的关键信息填写在相应位置上。录音听两遍。

content.content:
Travelling
Where to travel_____.
Time to travel there_____.
The weather there_____.
Travel with whom_____.
The most famous placeTerra-cotta Warriors and Horses _____.
content.contentDesc:
M: Hi, Jenny. Did you have fun on your vacation?

W: Yes, I did. I went to Xi'an with my brother.

M: How did you like it?

W: Everything was really interesting. Terra-cotta Warriors and Horses Museum is the most famous place of interest. It was built by the first emperor of China, Yingzheng. And the warriors and horses are all made of china and clay. The food in Xi'an is also wonderful. The weather there in spring is neither too cold nor too hot. You won't feel disappointed if you go there.

M: Yes, I also like the museum. And I wish to go there some day.

answers.answer: Neither too cold nor too hot
subAnswers: Neither too cold nor too hot

answerList: Neither too cold nor too hot

answers: Neither too cold nor too hot

content.contentDesc:
W: I have a very humorous friend. He can always make me laugh by telling jokes. What kind of friend do you like best, Henry?

M: Well, I am a serious person, so I like someone with a sense of humor, too.

W: Why do you say so?

M: It is because I feel relaxed when I talk to them. They can always bring me optimistic emotions. This makes me happy.

subContents.content: What kind of friend does Henry like best?
Why does Henry like his friend?

options.option: Because he feels relaxed when he talk to them.
Because they can bring him optimistic emotions.

W: Oh, you should give him another chance. After all, he is only a child.
